Supporting more actions like creating new env, installing packages will not be very difficult and make super sense to have. but i'd like to leave them as future work.

@astroshim @bzz @1ambda 
- Now I added a start-zeppelin.script to zeppelin-base image. It allow user to modify some configs by passing env variables. Also the user can share the logs and notebook folder in the container to the host machine by passing `-v $PWD/logs:path-in-docker/logs`. So you can share the spark folder to the container and assign `SPARK_HOME` in the container; according to what @khalidhuseynov have suggested. 
- And I think the previous issue needs more investigation.

@felizbear 

Something is happening while building `zeppelin-web` module

```
// recently passed PR CI: https://travis-ci.org/apache/zeppelin/builds/177018840
